character
  1. The upper case letter šⲁⲓ (ϣⲁⲓ), the 25th letter of the Coptic alphabet.

character
  1. The lower case letter šⲁⲓ (ϣⲁⲓ), the 25th letter of the Coptic alphabet.

name
  1. (Fayyumic) Sekhmet the Egyptian goddess of war, protection, healing, and rage. She is the wife of Ptah and mother of Nefertem and Maahes.

column2:
name
  1. (Sahidic) Sekhmet the Egyptian goddess of war, protection, healing, and rage. She is the wife of Ptah and mother of Nefertem and Maahes.

name
  1. (Bohairic, Sahidic) Khonsu, the Egyptian traveller god, god of time, the moon, and travelling.

verb
  1. (Bohairic, Sahidic) to plait.
  2. (Bohairic, Sahidic) to fight.

noun
  1. (Bohairic, Sahidic) a fight.
  2. (Bohairic, Sahidic) difficulty, trial.

column2:
character
  1. The upper case letter hori (ϩⲟⲣⲓ), the 28th letter of the Coptic alphabet.

character
  1. The lower case letter hori (ϩⲟⲣⲓ), the 28th letter of the Coptic alphabet.

noun
  1. (Sahidic) Hades, the Greek god of the dead and the underworld

name
  1. (Fayyumic) Hathor, the Egyptian goddess of joy, love, and motherhood.
  2. (Fayyumic) March.

name
  1. (Bohairic, Sahidic) Hathor, the Egyptian goddess of joy, love, and motherhood.
  2. (Bohairic, Sahidic) March.

noun
  1. (Old Coptic) humankind
  2. (Old Coptic) people of a given place
  3. (Old Coptic) sun-folk

noun
  1. (Fayyumic) man, male (human or god)
  2. (Fayyumic) man, husband

adj
  1. (Fayyumic) male
  2. (Fayyumic) wild

name
  1. (Sahidic): the Apis bull, a bull worshipped as a herald of the gods (first Ptah, then Osiris, then Atum).

name
  1. (Bohairic): the Apis bull, a bull worshipped as a herald of the gods (first Ptah, then Osiris, then Atum).

name
  1. (Sahidic, Fayyumic, Bohairic) Hermes, the greek god of roads, athletes, journeys, thieves, trickery, commerce and herding. He is the son of Zeus and Maia.
  2. (astronomy) the planet Mercury.

column2:
noun
  1. (Bohairic) reconciliation, peace

verb
  1. (Bohairic) to reconcile, to make peace

character
  1. The upper case letter janjia (ϫⲁⲛϫⲓⲁ), the 29th letter of the Coptic alphabet.

character
  1. The lower case letter janjia (ϫⲁⲛϫⲓⲁ), the 29th letter of the Coptic alphabet.

noun
  1. (Fayyumic, Akhmimic, Lycopolitan) master
  2. (Fayyumic, Akhmimic, Lycopolitan) lord
  3. (Fayyumic, Akhmimic, Lycopolitan, Christianity, always with definite article) Lord

column2:
character
  1. The supralinear stroke, placed over a syllabic consonant.

name
  1. (Sahidic) Athena, Greek goddess of war, battle tactics, and wisdom.

character
  1. The lower case letter alpha (ⲁ), the 1st letter of the Coptic alphabet.

particle
  1. indicates the affirmative past

name
  1. (Judaism) The tenth month of the civil year and the fourth month of the ecclesiastical year in the Jewish calendar, after Tammuz and before Elul.

noun
  1. (Sahidic, Bohairic, formal) Alternative form of ⲁⲡⲁ (apa)

noun
  1. (Sahidic, Bohairic) agora, marketplace and social hub, forum

noun
  1. contest, race
  2. (Christianity) struggle, tribulation (usually in reference to martyrdom)

name
  1. (Sahidic) Adonis, a Greek mythological hero and lover of Aphrodite.

noun
  1. (Akhmimic, Fayyumic, Lycopolitan, countable) a loaf of bread
  2. (Akhmimic, Fayyumic, Lycopolitan, uncountable) bread

name
  1. (Sahidic) Athena, Greek goddess of war, battle tactics, and wisdom.

name
  1. (Bohairic) Hathor, the Egyptian goddess of joy, love, and motherhood.
  2. (Bohairic) March.

verb
  1. to increase in size
  2. to advance in age

noun
  1. (Fayyumic, countable) a loaf of bread
  2. (Fayyumic, uncountable) bread

noun
  1. (Fayyumic) oipe, a dry measure of volume equivalent to 4 heqat (about 19.2 litres).

verb
  1. (Fayyumic) to keep, to guard
  2. (Fayyumic) to study, to learn

noun
  1. (Fayyumic) watch, guard

name
  1. In particular, the name of a Judean queen.

name
  1. In particular, the name of several greek kings.

name
  1. (356–323 BCE) A king (basileus) of the Ancient Greek kingdom of Macedon and conqueror of much of Asia.

name
  1. an epithet of Apollo in his nature as a healer god.

column2:
name
  1. (Bohairic) Amun, the hidden king of the Egyptian gods
  2. (Bohairic) Thebes, Egypt. Derived from Amun's role as the patron god of Thebes.

name
  1. (Sahidic) Amun, the hidden king of the Egyptian gods, the god of mercy, forgiveness, and hiddenness.
  2. (Sahidic) Thebes, Egypt. Derived from Amun's role as the patron god of Thebes.

name
  1. (Sahidic) Anhur, the Egyptian god of war

name
  1. (Bohairic) Anhur, the Egyptian god of war

name
  1. (Sahidic) Anat, an ancient Semitic goddess of war and fertility.

verb
  1. (intransitive, Sahidic) to live as an anachorite (hermit)

name
  1. In particular, the name of several byzantine emperors.

name
  1. A male lover of the roman emperor, Hadrian, later deified after his death.

name
  1. In particular, the name of several greek kings.

noun
  1. (Sahidic, Bohairic, Fayyumic) apa (a title used for male clergy or saints in the Coptic Church)

name
  1. (usually with definite article) Apollo, the Greco-Roman god of light, music, art, and prophecy.

column2:
verb
  1. (Sahidic, Bohairic) to keep, to guard
  2. (Bohairic) to study, to learn

noun
  1. (Sahidic, Bohairic) watch, guard

name
  1. (Sahidic): Ares, the Greek god of war, violence, and bloodlust.

name
  1. (Sahidic, Bohairic, Fayyumic) Ares Anhur, the syncronization of the greek god Ares and the egyptian god Anhur worshipped in Ptolemaic Egypt.

name
  1. (Sahidic, Bohairic, Fayyumic) Ariadne, wife of the god Dionysus and goddess of the maze.

name
  1. in particular, the eldest son of John Hyrcanus.

name
  1. In particular, the name of an early Athenian comedian, poet, and playwright.

name
  1. In particular, the name of a roman emperor.

noun
  1. (Bohairic) master of a feast (who presides at the table)

name
  1. (Bohairic, Sahidic, Fayyumic) Ashkelon, a city in Israel.

name
  1. (Sahidic) Asclepius, Greek god of healing and medicine.

name
  1. (Sahidic) Atum, the Egyptian god of creation, destruction, and the creator of the Nile river.

noun
  1. (Bohairic) (anatomy) head (part of the body)
  2. (Bohairic) magistrate, headman, chief

name
  1. in particular, a mythological figure of the Iliad

prefix
  1. (Sahidic, Akhmimic, Lycopolitan, Fayyumic, Bohairic) verbal prefix of perfect, pluperfect and aorist tenses

name
  1. (Sahidic) Baal, king of the Levantine gods and god of the sky, lightning, war, and fertility.

noun
  1. (Sahidic, Bohairic, Akhmimic, Fayyumic, Old Coptic) baptism

name
  1. (biblical) Bartholomew, One of the Twelve Apostles.

column2:
name
  1. (history) a general of the Byzantine Empire, who was instrumental to Emperor Justinian's ambitious project of reconquering much of the Mediterranean territory of the former Western Roman Empire, which had been lost less than a century previously.

name
  1. Bes, an ancient Egyptian god, the protector of households and mothers, children and childbirth

verb
  1. (Sahidic, Akhmimic, Lycopolitan, Bohairic, Fayyumic, Old Coptic) to loosen, to untie
  2. (Sahidic, Akhmimic, Lycopolitan, Bohairic, Fayyumic, Old Coptic) to melt
  3. (Sahidic, Akhmimic, Lycopolitan, Bohairic, Fayyumic, Old Coptic) to unstring

name
  1. (Bohairic, Sahidic, Fayyumic) Galilee, a region in Israel.

name
  1. Gamelion: the seventh month of the Attic calendar, corresponding to the lunar term around January and February

conj
  1. (postpositive, usually second word in a clause) for, because

name
  1. (Sahidic) Geb, the Egyptian god of the Earth.

column2:
verb
  1. (Sahidic, Fayyumic, Lycopolitan) may it happen (introduces wish)

name
  1. (Sahidic) Gaia, the greek goddess of the Earth.
  2. (Sahidic) Earth.
  3. (Sahidic) land

noun
  1. (Sahidic) laurel, the leaves.
  2. (Sahidic) a laurel wreath.

name
  1. (Sahidic) Dagon, The main god of the Phoenicians. Although at one time believed to be represented as half man and half fish, modern scholarship recognizes that the latter was the apkallu, while Dagan/Dagon was a grain god.

name
  1. In particular, the name of a Coptic Orthodox Pope.

name
  1. (biblical) The second king of Judah and Israel, the successor of Saul in the Old Testament.

particle
  1. indicates a shift in topic, sometimes translated as: but, and, now but often left untranslated.

name
  1. (Bohairic, Sahidic) Diana, the Roman goddess of hunting and the moon

name
  1. In particular, The name of a roman emperor.

name
  1. in particular, a mythological figure of the Iliad

name
  1. in particular, a mythological figure of the Iliad

name
  1. (Sahidic) Dionysus, Greek god of wine, the vine, theatre, ritual madness, and fertility.

name
  1. (Sahidic, Bohairic, Fayyumic) Dionysus, Greek god of wine, the vine, theatre, ritual madness, and fertility. Seen in Egypt as a god of immortality. Associated with Osiris and Serapis by Herodotus and in the Greco-Roman period.

name
  1. (Sahidic, Bohairic, Fayyumic) The Dioscuri, the half-immortal twins Castor and Pollux, who were worshiped in Fayyum and Naucratis.
  2. In particular, the name of two Coptic Orthodox Popes.

verb
  1. (Sahidic, Akhmimic, Lycopolitan) to make
  2. (Sahidic, Akhmimic, Lycopolitan) to do

noun
  1. (Sahidic, Akhmimic, Lycopolitan) father
  2. (Sahidic, Akhmimic, Lycopolitan, in the plural) parent (of unspecified sex)
  3. (Sahidic, Akhmimic, Lycopolitan) title applied to religious leaders and monks
  4. (Sahidic, Akhmimic, Lycopolitan) title applied to Biblical figures and saints
  5. (Sahidic, Lycopolitan) barley

noun
  1. (Bohairic, Sahidic, Fayyumic) builder, mason
  2. (Bohairic, Sahidic, Fayyumic) potter

prep
  1. (Bohairic) to the other side (of), over, across, beyond

verb
  1. (Sahidic, Akhmimic) to keep, to guard.
  2. (Akhmimic) to study, to learn.

noun
  1. (Sahidic, Akhmimic) watch, guard.

column2:
verb
  1. (Bohairic) to be a witness, to bear witness

name
  1. (Sahidic, Fayyumic, Bohairic) Hermes, the greek god of roads, athletes, journeys, thieves, trickery, and herding. He is the son of Zeus and Maia.
  2. (astronomy) the planet Mercury.

column2:
name
  1. (Sahidic): Iris, messanger of the Greek Gods and goddess of the rainbow.

noun
  1. (Sahidic, Bohairic, Fayyumic) ground, earth, dust, rubbish

name
  1. (Bohairic, Sahidic) Juno, the Roman goddess of marriage and childbirth and the queen of the Roman gods. Roman equivalent to Hera.

noun
  1. (Bohairic, Sahidic) reed, rush, particularly Saccharum aegypticum
  2. (Bohairic, Sahidic) pencil

noun
  1. (Sahidic, Akhmimic, Lycopolitan) Earth, as opposed to other celestial bodies or heaven
  2. (Sahidic, Akhmimic, Lycopolitan) earth, soil
  3. (Sahidic) district, province

noun
  1. (Bohairic) earth, land, country
  2. (Bohairic) district, province

name
  1. (Bohairic) the planet Earth.

column2:
noun
  1. (Bohairic) hood, cowl
  2. (Bohairic) a kind of headdress consisting of a small cap environed by a gigantic turban, a bonnet, popular with the Ayyubids and Mamluks

name
  1. In particular, the name of a roman emperor.

verb
  1. (Bohairic) to turn, to go around

name
  1. In particular, the name of a roman emperor.

column2:
noun
  1. (Sahidic, Bohairic) crown, coping, battlement

verb
  1. (Sahidic, Bohairic, transitive, intransitive) to set a crown upon, adorn

noun
  1. (Sahidic) mother
  2. (Sahidic) title applied to religious leaders
  3. (Sahidic, of bees) queen bee

noun
  1. disciple
  2. (specifically) any of the Twelve, the disciples of Jesus

name
  1. (Sahidic) Macedonia, a land in the north of Greece.

adj
  1. (Sahidic) effeminate

noun
  1. (Sahidic) catamite, bottom (passive male partner in homosexual intercourse)

noun
  1. (Bohairic, Sahidic) place of lying, couch
  2. (Bohairic, Sahidic) bedroom
  3. (Bohairic, Sahidic) cohabitation

column2:
verb
  1. (Bohairic) to look at, to see
  2. (Bohairic) to perceive

noun
  1. vision

pron
  1. (postpositive) they
  2. used as 3rd person plural pronominal copula in verbless clauses

name
  1. (Sahidic) The god Nefertum, personification of the first plant, a lotus, that mythically bloomed after the primeval waters receded and gave rise to the sun.

column2:
noun
  1. (Sahidic) safety

verb
  1. (Sahidic) to be saved, to be safe, to escape
  2. (Sahidic) to save, to preserve

noun
  1. (Bohairic, Fayyumic) a god

name
  1. (Bohairic, Fayyumic, with definite article) God

noun
  1. (Sahidic, Bohairic, Fayyumic, Akhmimic, Lycopolitan) gold
  2. (by extension) money

name
  1. Nubia, Nobatia (a region of Egypt, Sudan; former country in Africa)

noun
  1. abyss (of hell)
  2. depth (of the Earth or sea)

name
  1. (Sahidic) Nu, the egyptian god of primeval abyss.

column2:
name
  1. (Bohairic) Pathros, a part of Thebaid in Upper Egypt extending from Elephantine to Asyut or Abidos.

name
  1. An epithet of Athena, meaning "she who brandishes".

name
  1. (Sahidic) Pan, the Greek God of shepherds and forests.

noun
  1. (Bohairic) camp, encampment (military)

name
  1. (Bohairic) Al Burumbul (a town in Egypt)

name
  1. (Sahidic) Parthenon, the famous temple to Athena which resides in Athens.

noun
  1. (biblical) patriarch, biblical characters regarded as the immediate forefathers of the Hebrews
  2. (Christianity) patriarch, bishop of a see of the Pentarchy

name
  1. in particular, a mythological figure of the Iliad. He is the main companion and lover of the warrior, Achilles.

noun
  1. (Sahidic, Akhmimic, Lycopolitan, Bohairic) father
  2. (Sahidic, Akhmimic, Lycopolitan, Bohairic, in the plural) parent (of unspecified sex)
  3. (Sahidic, Akhmimic, Lycopolitan, Bohairic) title applied to religious leaders and monks
  4. (Sahidic, Akhmimic, Lycopolitan, Bohairic) title applied to Biblical figures and saints

pron
  1. (postpositive) he
  2. used as 3rd person masculine singular pronominal copula in verbless clauses

noun
  1. (Sahidic) heaven, sky

name
  1. (Sahidic) Muse, greek goddesses of poetry, music, and the arts.

name
  1. (Greek mythology) The mythological Greek warrior who slew the Gorgon Medusa by decapitating her. He married Andromeda after rescuing her from Ceto and founded Mycenae. He was the son of Zeus and Danae.
  2. The last Antigonid king of Macedonia, Perseus of Macedon.

name
  1. (Sahidic) Persephone, the Greek goddess of death and queen of the underworld.

adj
  1. (Bohairic, Sahidic) Persian
  2. (Bohairic) Ayyubid

noun
  1. (Bohairic, Sahidic) Persian
  2. (Bohairic) Ayyubid dynasty

name
  1. (Sahidic) Petbe, the Egyptian god of revenge.

column2:
noun
  1. (Sahidic) cleansing

verb
  1. (Sahidic) to be clean, to cleanse, to wash

noun
  1. (Sahidic, Akhmimic, Lycopolitan, Old Coptic) human, person
  2. (Sahidic, Akhmimic, Lycopolitan, Old Coptic) anyone
  3. (Sahidic, Akhmimic, Lycopolitan, Old Coptic, with possessive article) closely associated person: kinsman, servant, friend

adj
  1. (Sahidic, Akhmimic, Lycopolitan, Old Coptic) human

noun
  1. (Bohairic, sometimes Fayyumic) human, human being
  2. (Bohairic, sometimes Fayyumic) man, male

name

column2:
noun
  1. (Bohairic) word
  2. (Bohairic) account, retelling of an event

verb
  1. (Bohairic, transitive) to speak
  2. (Bohairic, transitive) to declare
  3. (Bohairic, transitive) to preach
  4. (Bohairic) recount

noun
  1. (Fayyumic, astronomy) Sirius, A bluish-white star in the constellation Canis Major; Alpha (α) Canis Majoris. A vertex of the Winter Triangle and the brightest star in the night sky.

noun
  1. (Bohairic) stater, a type of Greek coin

name
  1. A name ascribed to the stepdaughter of Herod who asked for the execution of John the Baptist.
  2. (biblical) A woman mentioned in Mark 16:1, present at the crucifixion of Christ.

name
  1. (Sahidic) Samothrace, An island in Greece, in the Aegean Sea.

name
  1. (Sahidic, Bohairic): Serapis, Graeco-Egyptian god of death, healing, benevolence, and rebirth. The greek synchronization of Osiris and the Apis bull.

noun
  1. (Sahidic) stater, a type of Greek coin

name
  1. (Sahidic, Old Coptic) Sekhmet the Egyptian goddess of war, protection, healing, and rage. She is the wife of Ptah and mother of Nefertem and Maahes.

adv
  1. (Bohairic, Sahidic, Akhmimic, Lycopolitan, Oxyrhynchite) yes, indeed

name

noun
  1. (Bohairic, astronomy) Sirius, A bluish-white star in the constellation Canis Major; Alpha (α) Canis Majoris. A vertex of the Winter Triangle and the brightest star in the night sky.

noun
  1. (Bohairic) a fermented drink from cereals: ale, beer

noun
  1. (Sahidic) a fermented drink from cereals: ale, beer

noun
  1. (Bohairic) laughter, play
  2. (Bohairic) derision, mockery

verb
  1. (Bohairic) to laugh, to play
  2. (Bohairic) to deride, to mock

noun

  2. (Sahidic, Akhmimic, Fayyumic, Lycopolitan) (female) cousin
  3. (Sahidic, Akhmimic, Fayyumic, Lycopolitan) wife

column2:
noun
  1. (Akhmimic, Fayyumic) mountain
  2. (Akhmimic, Fayyumic) desert
  3. (Akhmimic, Fayyumic) monastery

verb
  1. (intransitive, Fayyumic) to buy

noun
  1. (Sahidic) bull, ox

name
  1. (Sahidic) An epithet of Dionysus, relating to his association with bulls.

pron
  1. (postpositive) she
  2. used as 3rd person feminine singular pronominal copula in verbless clauses

verb
  1. (Akhmimic) Alternative form of ϯ (ti).

noun
  1. (Bohairic) Tatar, of Tatar heritage
  2. (Bohairic) Tatar language

adj
  1. (Bohairic) Tatar

name
  1. (Old Coptic, Sahidic, Bohairic) The Duat, the Egyptian afterlife realm.

name
  1. In particular, the name of a roman emperor.

noun
  1. (Bohairic) sum of money, sum of silver

noun
  1. (Fayyumic) sum of money, sum of silver

name
  1. (Sahidic) Cyrene, an ancient greek city in Libya.

noun
  1. (Sahidic) a multitude
  2. (Sahidic) the world
  3. (Sahidic) a variety

noun
  1. (Sahidic) border, limit
  2. (Sahidic) nome
  3. (Sahidic) province, district, suburb
  4. (Sahidic) bishopric

noun
  1. (Bohairic) Turk, of Turkish heritage
  2. (Bohairic) Turkish language

adj
  1. (Bohairic) Turkish

name
  1. An epithet of Hermes, meaning thrice great. Adaptation of an epithet of Thoth, twice-great.

name
  1. (Sahidic) The Biga peninsula in the northwestern part of Anatolia, Turkey.

name
  1. (Bohairic) Ghana (a region of West Africa) on the shores of the Senegal river.

name
  1. (Sahidic, Bohairic, Fayyumic) Tyre, a city in Lebanon.

noun
  1. (Sahidic) fortune
  2. (Sahidic) luck

name
  1. (Sahidic) Tyche, Lady Luck, Fortuna, goddess of luck and fortune.

name
  1. (Sahidic) Chimera, a monstrous fire-breathing hybrid creature of goat, snake, and lion.

noun
  1. (Bohairic) smoke, mist, obscurity
  2. (Bohairic) tobacco (Coined by Zeniya Copts in ca. 1600)

verb
  1. (transitive, Bohairic) to dismiss
  2. (intransitive, Bohairic) to become loose
  3. (Bohairic) to forgive

noun
  1. (Bohairic, Sahidic) town, district.
  2. (Bohairic, Sahidic) rural administrative district, village (after Arab conquest).

noun
  1. (biblical) psalm, chapter from the Book of Psalms
